    <p>Buy: Or­der by send­ing a What­sApp mes­sage to 9010-2901 Info: lyn­netteskitc­hen.com In­gre­di­ents: Hokkaido dried scal­lops, dried shrimp, ba­con, Thai chilli flakes, Shaox­ing wine, Thai fish sauce, brown su­gar, sea salt, home­made chicken stock and sun­flower oil</p>
    <p>Score: 21.5/30</p>
    <p>What the judges say: Ms Joanne Toh: “This sauce has a nice bal­ance of salti­ness and spice.”</p>
    <p>About the sauce: Ms Lyn­nette Seah, 63, who runs pri­vate din­ing busi­ness Lyn­nette’s Kitchen, started sell­ing XO sauce dur­ing the cir­cuit breaker pe­riod, re­work­ing a recipe she got from a Hong Kong home chef.</p>
    <p>Each batch takes her 41/ hours</p>
    <p>2 to make.</p>
    <p>Her favourite XO sauce is from Hua Ting, the Chi­nese restau­rant at Or­chard Ho­tel, where she likes to have it with dim­sum. “It is so tasty and it adds more oomph to dumplings. I love it fried with car­rot turnip cake too,” she says. “I feel mine is close to it, with ex­tra chilli and ba­con to suit my taste.”</p>

